    "body": "## Problem\r\n'shellcmdflag' is not set according to the value of 'shell' as described in the doc.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nVim has some detection logic for this, but it was already lost in nvim's first commit. This may also involve the format of 'shell' option, along with several potentially related issues, I've beend digging into it to see how this should be handled.\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\r\n  If this is your first time, check out https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\r\n  for our PR guidelines.\r\n-->\r\n\r\ntry to close #31528, close #28384, close #16957",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Vim has some detection logic for this, but it was already lost in nvim's first commit\r\n\r\nthe logic can end up being quite a mess.\r\n\r\ni wouldn't spend much time on this. or if we really do want it, i would move the logic to Lua, and call it via `nlua_call_excmd` or `nlua_call_vimfn`",
